<p>The <b>ring ouzel</b> (<i>Turdus torquatus</i>) is a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Europe" title="Europe">European</a> member of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thrush_(bird)" title="Thrush (bird)">thrush</a> family Turdidae. It is the mountain equivalent of the closely related <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Common_blackbird" title="Common blackbird">common blackbird</a>, and breeds in gullies, rocky areas or scree slopes.</p>
<p></p>
